</p></section>
<section class="text-flow"><h2>4. Server logs</h2><ul class="sectionList">
<li><b>Data processed:</b> IP address, date/time, requested URL, referrer, user agent, status code, transferred data volume.</li>
<li><b>Purpose:</b> ensuring technical stability and security (e.g., attack detection, troubleshooting).</li>
<li><b>Retention:</b> typically short-term; logs are deleted or anonymised as soon as no longer required for the purpose (hosting/security).</li>
</ul></section>
<section class="text-flow"><h2>5. Google Tag Manager (GTM)</h2><p>
  We use Google Tag Manager (Google Ireland Limited, Dublin, Ireland) to manage website tags.
  GTM itself typically does not set analytics cookies, but it can trigger other services.
  Non-essential measurement tags are activated only after consent (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR).
</p></section>
<section class="text-flow"><h2>6. Third-country transfers (e.g., USA)</h2><p>
  When using Google services, transfers of personal data to third countries (especially the USA) cannot be ruled out.
  Where required, transfers are based on appropriate safeguards (e.g., EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework or Standard Contractual Clauses under Art. 46 GDPR).
</p></section>
